This paper deals with the problem of time scheduling in a cognitive radio network, which involves optimizing the use of available resources to maximize network throughput. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given that the paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning algorithm to solve the problem, cs.NI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. However, cs.IT, cs.SY, and cs.AI are also relevant due to the technical nature of the problem and the methods used to solve it.
